                <h1>Explore the Diverse World of Greek Gods and Goddesses</h1>
                <p>The ancient Greek pantheon features a rich tapestry of gods and goddesses, each embodying distinct aspects of life and nature. Zeus, the king of the gods, rules the sky, while Hera, his queen, governs marriage. Poseidon controls the seas, and Athena symbolizes wisdom and war. Other notable deities include Apollo, Artemis, and Hades, each with their unique myths, stories, and attributes.</p>
